div.div:
How does access control work?
The API can be accessed independently by multiple, unrelated client systems.
To handle fine-grained access control, IAM Resource Policy is attached to API Gateway REST API. The policy allows client systems to access (HTTP POST) their dedicated client-specific paths
( /clients/{clientPartition}/* ).
The policy consists of multiple statements. There is 1 statement for each client system. Each statement grants access to a specific REST API path based on client-specific:
1. AWS Account
2. VPC Endpoint
